To setup a VM from Vagrant you need to download vagrant into your OS:

create a folder for Vagrant: (root folder permission required in case windows.)

Run following commands:

mkdir Vagrant

cd Vagrant

vagrant init image_name (like: generic/ubunbu2204)

vagrant up

vagrant destroy

vagrant box remove generic/ubuntu2204 --provider=hyperv

For running VMs and to extract VM IDs:
vagrant global-status

To remove 


For UBUNTU:

sudo apt-add-repository "deb [arch=amd64] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main"
sudo apt update
sudo apt install vagrant -y

#To show available boxes in your system:

vagrant box list

centos/7
generic/ubuntu2204

#To delete a VM:

vagrant halt VM_ID


#Basic Vagrant commands
vagrant init [name [url]]
vagrant up [name|id]
vagrant status [name|id]
vagrant halt [name|id]
vagrant destroy [name|id]
vagrant ssh [name|id]
vagrant suspend [name|id]
vagrant resume [name|id]






